    "voice": "Liturgically precise, Hebrew-forward, chant-oriented, traditional, and visually dependent on vocalization and trope marks.",
    "bestUses": [
      "Optional Hebrew chant panels for ritually experienced hosts",
      "Traditional-theme call-and-response and song selections",
      "Facilitator editions that explicitly teach how a passage is sung"
    ],
    "beginnerRisks": [
      "The extracted text is principally Hebrew and cannot orient an English-only first-time host by itself.",
      "Cantillation marks need correct font rendering and may be lost or made confusing by careless line wrapping.",
      "Long traditional passages include assumptions and ritual details that require an accessible English explanation."
    ],
    "politicalContext": "Traditional biblical, land, temple, and Jerusalem language appears as liturgy rather than modern political advocacy. Any Jerusalem refrain must obey the project rule limiting it to a traditional selection without a social-justice override.",
